00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:57,280
I love you.

19
00:01:58,250 --> 00:01:59,350
I'll use this one.

20
00:01:59,350 --> 00:02:02,890
Mom, aren't you on the night shift? Why are you back so early?

21
00:02:02,890 --> 00:02:05,370
Are you sure it's your mom?

22
00:02:05,370 --> 00:02:08,500
Dad! Dad!

23
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:10,950
Weren't you coming back? Why did you suddenly come back?

24
00:02:10,950 --> 00:02:13,982
It's your mom's birthday. I wanted to surprise her. How could I not come?

25
00:02:13,982 --> 00:02:17,570
Dad! Listen. I've got everything ready.

26
00:02:17,570 --> 00:02:18,920
That's great!

27
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:20,790
- Hurry, give it to me! 
 - Let me wash my hands first.

28
00:02:20,790 --> 00:02:27,700
You have no idea how hard it is for me to take time off.

29
00:02:27,700 --> 00:02:28,920
What happened, Dad?

30
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:30,670
Huan Er.

31
00:02:30,670 --> 00:02:34,920
Why are my mouth-rinsing cup, toothbrush, and towel gone from the washroom?

32
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:35,940
Where did they go?

33
00:02:35,940 --> 00:02:39,070
Mom said the washroom was too crowded there, so she put them away.

34
00:02:39,070 --> 00:02:41,070
- Let me call and ask her. 
 - Don't!

35
00:02:41,070 --> 00:02:43,450
Don't call her. If you do, the surprise will be ruined.

36
00:02:43,450 --> 00:02:45,280
Yeah, you're right!

37
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:49,850
You see, I hardly ever come home, and now I feel like this isn't even my house.

38
00:02:49,850 --> 00:02:52,140
Dad, I'll go and buy you a new set.

39
00:02:52,140 --> 00:02:54,130
- Don't! Forget it. 
 - It's just downstairs.

40
00:02:54,130 --> 00:02:55,920
It's late now. It's not safe.

41
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:57,180
I have a solution.

42
00:02:57,180 --> 00:02:59,660
What is it?

43
00:02:59,660 --> 00:03:00,990
I'll rub my teeth with my fingers; that'll do.

44
00:03:00,990 --> 00:03:03,720
Dad, don't be disgusting.

45
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:07,450
Your mom is unreasonable for putting all my stuff away.

46
00:03:13,110 --> 00:03:15,690
Luckily, no one noticed.

47
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:29,570
Oh my god.

48
00:03:29,570 --> 00:03:31,730
Huan Er, is there any milk left?

49
00:03:31,730 --> 00:03:33,920
This milk expired days ago.

50
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:35,800
Dad, try looking for it again.

51
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,940
Doesn't your mom cook for you?

52
00:03:37,940 --> 00:03:41,320
I've just found five or six bottles of expired stuff here.

53
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:44,830
Also, this spatula wasn't cleaned properly after being used.

54
00:03:44,830 --> 00:03:47,640
Is your mom mistreating you at home or what?

55
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:50,600
How am I abusing her?

56
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:52,240
Wherever you came from, go back there!

57
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:54,260
 Mistreating her? If you're not happy, take her away! 

58
00:03:54,260 --> 00:03:57,420
- Look, this is expired. 
 - I'm playing both the mom and dad roles.

59
00:03:57,420 --> 00:03:59,890
- It's not easy for me. 
 - Do you think it's easy for me?

60
00:03:59,890 --> 00:04:02,490
Please, come back to the topic. This milk is expired.

61
00:04:02,490 --> 00:04:05,600
So what? I'll use it as fertilizer for the plants! I didn't give it to her to drink!

62
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:09,070
- Are you just arguing for the sake of it? 
 - You're barely ever home all year,

63
00:04:09,070 --> 00:04:10,260
and you have the nerve to lecture me?

64
00:04:10,260 --> 00:04:11,900
What do you mean? Why am I never home?

65
00:04:11,900 --> 00:04:15,860
I work hard all year. I raise the kid and take care of her.

66
00:04:15,860 --> 00:04:17,500
I live like a widow. Is it easy for me?

67
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,670
You've gone overboard. A widow? Then, who am I here?

68
00:04:19,670 --> 00:04:21,640
- I'm just like a widow. 
 - Aren't I out there earning money?

69
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:22,860
Earning money? Give it to me.

70
00:04:22,860 --> 00:04:24,600
- I gave you all the money! 
 - That little bit?

71
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,710
I gave you money and you bought such a thing?

72
00:04:26,710 --> 00:04:28,756
- Why can't I buy this? 
 - This could poison someone.

73
00:04:28,756 --> 00:04:29,840
What's wrong with you?

74
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:31,580
 All you buy is expired stuff. 

75
00:04:31,580 --> 00:04:33,320
 How was I supposed to know it was expired? 

76
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:35,860
 I don't want to argue with you anymore. I just got off my night shift. 

77
00:04:35,860 --> 00:04:37,720
 I'll sleep first, then I'll argue with you later. 

78
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:40,500
 Stay or leave, it's up to you. 

79
00:04:50,010 --> 00:04:51,990
You scared me half to death!

80
00:04:51,990 --> 00:04:55,070
Morning. You wake up so early.

81
00:04:55,070 --> 00:04:56,790
Morning.

82
00:04:59,450 --> 00:05:02,060
Why are you up so early?

83
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:04,300
What else?

84
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:05,704
Taking out the trash.

85
00:05:05,704 --> 00:05:09,080
Oh yeah. You have to take out the trash.

86
00:05:11,820 --> 00:05:14,970
It's still early. Why are you in your pajamas

87
00:05:14,970 --> 00:05:16,720
and standing in front of my house?

88
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:18,450
I...

89
00:05:19,810 --> 00:05:21,960
I woke up early too.

90
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:24,700
Go on. Keep making things up.

91
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:26,480
Hold on, Chen Huan Er. That look on your face...

92
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:28,930
You really see me as just a brother, right?

93
00:05:28,930 --> 00:05:30,570
I...

94
00:05:31,260 --> 00:05:33,920
I just...

95
00:05:35,130 --> 00:05:37,690
wanted to ask you for tutoring.

96
00:05:41,610 --> 00:05:43,500
You...

97
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:47,358
want me... to tutor you?

98
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:50,670
You're talking nonsense in the morning. Are you sleepwalking?

99
00:05:50,670 --> 00:05:52,920
- Are you... 
 - Ouch! It's painful.

100
00:05:57,150 --> 00:05:59,720
My parents had a fight.

101
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:02,910
I just wanted to come here and hide for a bit.

102
00:06:02,910 --> 00:06:04,790
Is that okay?

103
00:06:22,890 --> 00:06:26,000
 Cong, come to my house! Chen Huan Er needs you. 

104
00:06:55,740 --> 00:07:00,280
Wait, should I change my outfits too?

105
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:03,560
Otherwise, I'm going to look out of place with you two.

106
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:06,890
Are you okay?

107
00:07:07,740 --> 00:07:10,600
I'm fine now.

108
00:07:11,790 --> 00:07:13,550
What's so funny?

109
00:07:13,550 --> 00:07:15,890
Nothing, go on.

110
00:07:15,890 --> 00:07:20,380
Sorry for waking you both up so early.

111
00:07:21,250 --> 00:07:25,490
I just don't understand why my parents suddenly started fighting.

112
00:07:25,490 --> 00:07:28,610
They used to argue, but never this bad.

113
00:07:28,610 --> 00:07:30,130
Why are they fighting?

114
00:07:30,130 --> 00:07:31,610
I don't know.

115
00:07:31,610 --> 00:07:33,440
When I woke up and started washing up,

116
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:35,852
my dad was making breakfast and my mom returned from her night shift.

117
00:07:35,852 --> 00:07:38,570
Then suddenly they started fighting.

118
00:07:38,570 --> 00:07:41,450
It feels like they argue because of me.

119
00:07:41,450 --> 00:07:44,860
Didn't you ask them why they were fighting?

120
00:07:44,860 --> 00:07:47,180
How am I supposed to ask?

121
00:07:47,890 --> 00:07:49,450
Fair point...

122
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:52,520
What about your parents?

123
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:54,500
What do they usually fight about?

124
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:56,230
My parents?

125
00:07:57,030 --> 00:07:59,050
My parents...

126
00:07:59,050 --> 00:08:03,370
Anything from international wars to the most trivial things.

127
00:08:03,370 --> 00:08:07,250
As long as they breathe the same air, they'll find a reason to argue.

128
00:08:07,250 --> 00:08:11,990
Usually, within a minute, my dad finds a way to coax my mom.

129
00:08:11,990 --> 00:08:15,940
And soon after he calms her down, within another minute, they'll start fighting again.

130
00:08:15,940 --> 00:08:18,460
Sometimes, it gets really dramatic.

131
00:08:18,460 --> 00:08:20,820
In our house, there's no fighting.

132
00:08:21,470 --> 00:08:23,450
Never?

133
00:08:23,450 --> 00:08:25,400
Never.

134
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:29,180
Every day, it's just my dad who gets scolded.

135
00:08:32,760 --> 00:08:37,970
Now that you mention it, I think my family isn't so bad after all.

136
00:08:37,970 --> 00:08:39,860
But what I really don't get is...

137
00:08:39,860 --> 00:08:43,620
if they can't stand each other so much,

138
00:08:43,620 --> 00:08:45,680
why did they choose to be together when they were young?

139
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:47,610
Haven't you heard the saying?

140
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:52,640
Many people say that before having kids, parents have a good relationship.

141
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:54,020
Who told you this nonsense?

142
00:08:54,020 --> 00:08:57,190
So, according to you, why did our parents have us?

143
00:08:57,190 --> 00:08:58,610
To suffer?

144
00:08:58,610 --> 00:09:00,250
Who knows?

145
00:09:00,250 --> 00:09:02,470
All beings endure suffering.

146
00:09:15,610 --> 00:09:20,690
Oh, right. Let me show you something I found last night.

147
00:09:26,020 --> 00:09:28,270
- Where is it? 
 - What is it?

148
00:09:29,950 --> 00:09:31,710
This and this.

149
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:36,780
Do you get it?

150
00:09:36,780 --> 00:09:42,090
So basically, your dad and your mom are actually fine.

151
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:51,060
Wait, does that mean...

152
00:09:56,040 --> 00:10:00,430
Your dad, and your mom?

153
00:10:00,430 --> 00:10:01,990
Are you crazy?

154
00:10:01,990 --> 00:10:03,400
My mom?

155
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:06,160
My mom?

156
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:07,350
My mom?

157
00:10:07,350 --> 00:10:10,070
How could that possibly be my mom?

158
00:10:15,280 --> 00:10:17,400
 All right, move a little this way. 

159
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:20,060
 - This way? 
 - Yeah, this background. 

160
00:10:20,060 --> 00:10:21,380
 All right. 

161
00:10:21,380 --> 00:10:23,160
 One, two... 

162
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:25,960
 No more film. 

163
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:28,230
 Sorry about that. Let me check if I have a spare roll. 

164
00:10:28,230 --> 00:10:29,230
 Hold on. 

165
00:10:29,230 --> 00:10:31,330
 No rush. Take your time. 

166
00:10:33,780 --> 00:10:43,710
 Yi Fan, why do I feel he has other intentions toward you? 

167
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:59,960
 Xi Chi. 

168
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:01,250
Good morning, Mom.

169
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:03,800
- Morning, Aunt Lin. 
 - Morning.

170
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:07,780
You three slept in this room last night?

171
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:10,779
Mom, what are you thinking?

172
00:11:10,779 --> 00:11:12,900
How could it be possible to fit three of us on my bed?

173
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:14,800
They just got here.

174
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:19,360
Just got here? Then you probably haven't had breakfast yet.

175
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:21,900
What do you want to eat? I'll make it for you.

176
00:11:23,070 --> 00:11:25,160
- Mom. 
 - What's wrong?

177
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:27,160
Can I ask you a question?

178
00:11:27,160 --> 00:11:35,400
Uncle Song... back when he was younger, did he... ever like you?

179
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:37,190
What?

180
00:11:48,730 --> 00:11:51,070
You're back for B and C again?

181
00:11:51,070 --> 00:11:53,230
What a special style you have!

182
00:11:53,230 --> 00:11:55,020
Why are you here?

183
00:11:55,020 --> 00:11:57,159
Delivering photos to Jing Xi Chi.

184
00:11:57,159 --> 00:11:58,590
I have something for you.

185
00:11:58,590 --> 00:12:02,140
Regarding the last math problem, I thought about it.

186
00:12:02,140 --> 00:12:05,010
I think that not everything needs an answer.

187
00:12:05,010 --> 00:12:08,360
What if the answer isn't what you want?

188
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,860
Study it carefully.

189
00:12:09,860 --> 00:12:12,040
This is all I can do to help.

190
00:12:14,210 --> 00:12:15,350
Jing Xi Chi.

191
00:12:15,350 --> 00:12:17,860
I'm here. Open the door.

