00:28:39,780 --> 00:28:43,790
♫  Is the faith she believes in  ♫

454
00:28:43,790 --> 00:28:51,740
♫  Remembering his silhouette still makes her heart race  ♫

455
00:28:51,740 --> 00:28:55,780
♫  The blank space in her heart  ♫

456
00:28:55,780 --> 00:28:59,760
♫  The expectations he once gave her  ♫

457
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:06,720
♫  Some things can never be defeated by time  ♫

458
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:10,243
♫  So what is love  ♫

459
00:29:11,120 --> 00:29:14,640
♫  What is love  ♫

460
00:30:08,600 --> 00:30:09,810
- Huan Er. 
 - Dad!

461
00:30:09,810 --> 00:30:11,514
You're back. Did you get wet in the rain?

462
00:30:11,514 --> 00:30:13,620
- Not really. 
 - Really? Your clothes are soaked.

463
00:30:13,620 --> 00:30:15,980
- Go home and change. 
 - Uncle Chen.

464
00:30:15,980 --> 00:30:17,560
- Hello. Go home and get changed. 
 - Bye, Uncle Chen.

465
00:30:17,560 --> 00:30:19,240
Don't catch a cold.

466
00:30:30,810 --> 00:30:33,460
All tidied up? The rain stopped.

467
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:38,480
- Didn't I tell you to change? Aren't you cold? 
 - It's fine, Dad. I didn't get too wet.

468
00:30:42,160 --> 00:30:45,540
Huan Er, I want to ask you something.

469
00:30:46,520 --> 00:30:50,500
It's so late already. What were you doing with that boy from the Jing family?

470
00:30:50,500 --> 00:30:52,530
He brought me something to eat.

471
00:30:52,530 --> 00:30:54,400
Dad, I've eaten so much.

472
00:30:54,400 --> 00:30:56,520
I feel like my stomach is going to explode.

473
00:30:57,080 --> 00:30:59,920
I can't take it, Dad. I need to go to the washroom.

474
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:03,050
Mom, are you done yet?

475
00:31:03,050 --> 00:31:04,740
Mom, hurry up!

476
00:31:04,740 --> 00:31:07,120
My stomach hurts.

477
00:31:07,120 --> 00:31:09,330
I can't hold it, Mom.

478
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:24,820
Li Qiang, bring a bed sheet.

479
00:31:25,610 --> 00:31:27,570
I just washed it. It's clean and dry now.

480
00:31:27,570 --> 00:31:29,660
There's definitely one over there. No need to bring that.

481
00:31:29,660 --> 00:31:31,060
Just listen to me.

482
00:31:31,060 --> 00:31:34,560
The bed sheets over there are always worn out and not as good as the ones at home.

483
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:36,200
What if you have an allergic reaction?

484
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:38,880
Dad, where are you going?

485
00:31:38,880 --> 00:31:39,950
I'm going on a work trip.

486
00:31:39,950 --> 00:31:41,390
Nonsense.

487
00:31:41,390 --> 00:31:43,060
Your dad has been transferred.

488
00:31:43,060 --> 00:31:44,630
Look how bad your department is.

489
00:31:44,630 --> 00:31:47,920
They just transferred you without prior notice. It was so sudden!

490
00:31:47,920 --> 00:31:49,240
I don't even know what to pack now.

491
00:31:49,240 --> 00:31:50,770
You got transferred, Dad?

492
00:31:50,770 --> 00:31:52,190
To Tonglin.

493
00:31:52,190 --> 00:31:55,260
Uncle Yang got promoted to deputy director,

494
00:31:55,260 --> 00:31:56,521
so they transferred me over there.

495
00:31:56,521 --> 00:31:59,660
If I do well, I might get promoted to deputy director too.

496
00:32:01,390 --> 00:32:04,990
I heard the sports university in Tonglin is quite good.

497
00:32:04,990 --> 00:32:08,430
I'm near the place. Let me check it out for you first.

498
00:32:08,430 --> 00:32:09,920
Got it.

499
00:32:12,810 --> 00:32:17,370
Li Qiang, I told you to bring more sweaters, but you didn't.

500
00:32:17,370 --> 00:32:20,670
It's just a quick check-in. No need to bring so much!

501
00:32:20,670 --> 00:32:24,070
You're always so stubborn with me. How stubborn you are.

502
00:32:26,780 --> 00:32:29,850
- Take care of your mom for me. 
 - Don't worry.

503
00:32:31,160 --> 00:32:33,280
I'm getting older now.

504
00:32:33,280 --> 00:32:35,300
I won't be going out to the field as much anymore.

505
00:32:35,300 --> 00:32:38,260
Once you start college, I'll transfer back,

506
00:32:38,260 --> 00:32:40,740
and we can all be together more often.

507
00:32:40,740 --> 00:32:43,820
- Oh, about your soccer— 
 - I know.

508
00:32:43,820 --> 00:32:45,900
Keep doing it until the end.

509
00:32:45,900 --> 00:32:47,580
I have to go now.

510
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:54,640
   

511
00:32:54,640 --> 00:32:57,120
You've grown taller.

512
00:32:57,120 --> 00:32:59,720
- Really? 
 - You look like an adult now.

513
00:33:02,060 --> 00:33:03,480
I'm off.

514
00:33:05,540 --> 00:33:06,960
Bye.

515
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:15,700
Where is Uncle Jing going?

516
00:33:15,700 --> 00:33:18,340
My dad was temporarily assigned out of town.

517
00:33:19,800 --> 00:33:21,990
When will he be back?

518
00:33:21,990 --> 00:33:23,400
Don't know.

519
00:33:24,580 --> 00:33:26,200
Where did you go?

520
00:33:26,200 --> 00:33:28,810
I bought a set of practice questions.

521
00:33:28,810 --> 00:33:30,390
Let's go.

522
00:33:36,810 --> 00:33:43,770
 I used to think I was the only one afraid to ask when Dad would come back. 

523
00:33:43,770 --> 00:33:48,240
 But I realized it's not just fear of the answer being too far away. 

524
00:33:51,090 --> 00:33:53,500
I'm home!

525
00:33:53,500 --> 00:33:55,470
Huan Er, you're back.

526
00:33:55,470 --> 00:33:56,710
Dad.

527
00:33:56,710 --> 00:33:59,480
Oh, right. Don't touch the kitchen door just yet.

528
00:33:59,480 --> 00:34:01,820
I just fixed it and put some oil on it.

529
00:34:01,820 --> 00:34:04,100
Why did you suddenly fix the door?

530
00:34:04,100 --> 00:34:07,060
Whenever you push this door, it creaks.

531
00:34:07,060 --> 00:34:09,900
If your mom comes home from a night shift for a nap,

532
00:34:09,900 --> 00:34:12,660
the creak will definitely wake her up.

533
00:34:12,660 --> 00:34:15,850
 I guess I was also worried that Dad, who already had so much on his mind, 

534
00:34:15,850 --> 00:34:19,700
 might hear it and feel even worse. 

535
00:34:22,390 --> 00:34:25,400
I'm leaving tomorrow, so I better get this done quickly.

536
00:34:25,400 --> 00:34:28,140
Oh yeah, I bought you some oranges.

537
00:34:28,140 --> 00:34:29,620
They're really sweet. Try one now.

538
00:34:29,620 --> 00:34:31,380
I'll try it.

539
00:34:33,810 --> 00:34:35,180
- It's so sweet. 
 - Right?

540
00:34:35,180 --> 00:34:36,320
- Try one. Try one. 
 - I'll have one.

541
00:34:36,320 --> 00:34:38,134
Sweet or not?

542
00:34:38,134 --> 00:34:39,830
- Sweet. 
 - Sweeter than me?

543
00:34:39,830 --> 00:34:42,580
Nothing's sweeter than my precious daughter.

544
00:34:43,390 --> 00:34:44,700
Dad, you're sweating so much.

545
00:34:44,700 --> 00:34:47,080
It's fine.

546
00:34:47,080 --> 00:34:48,800
Let me wipe it off for you.

547
00:34:48,800 --> 00:34:51,800
I'm getting VIP treatment. I have a little helper while working.

548
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:53,200
All done.

549
00:34:55,680 --> 00:34:57,660
Look, this is too loose.

550
00:34:59,140 --> 00:35:04,250
I told Mom she doesn't need to put your stuff away next time.

551
00:35:05,080 --> 00:35:07,920
It's okay, whatever is convenient for you two.

552
00:35:08,950 --> 00:35:10,355
Dad.

553
00:35:10,355 --> 00:35:12,620
Let's take a photo together.

554
00:35:12,620 --> 00:35:14,060
Why the sudden idea to take a picture?

555
00:35:14,060 --> 00:35:16,040
Well, I'm an adult now.

556
00:35:16,040 --> 00:35:17,390
I just want to keep a memory.

557
00:35:17,390 --> 00:35:20,280
- Can we? 
 - Sure, we'll take one later.

558
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:23,670
Wait a moment. Your neck is covered in sweat.

559
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:40,540
 I've realized I'll never ask that question aloud. 

560
00:35:40,540 --> 00:35:46,370
 Parents choose their dream careers and live the lives they want. It's their freedom. 

561
00:35:46,370 --> 00:35:51,370
 I can't choose my parents, but I can choose what kind of child to be. 

562
00:35:52,220 --> 00:35:56,390
 I choose to let them feel at ease. 

